9) Write a program that calculates the maximum of three numbers.

10) Write a program that receives three numbers as input and displays them in ascending order.

11) Write a program that receives three numbers as input and displays the two largest ones. Identify any special cases that may occur.

12) Write a program that receives three numbers as input and, if two of them have the same value, displays that value (the program displays nothing otherwise).

13) Write a program that displays the instant immediately following the current time.
    The program receives the current time as hours and minutes and displays the time corresponding to the next minute (remember that one minute after 10:59 is 11:00!).
    Assume everything happens on the same day (you do not need to check whether the current time is 23:59).

14) Explain what the programs below do by adding, for each output statement, a comment indicating the condition that must be satisfied for that statement to be executed.
    Notice how the absence of indentation can make reading difficult.

15) Write the code fragment that, if a is greater than 0, checks whether a equals 1 and, in that case, displays “a equals 1”; otherwise, if a is not greater than 0, displays “a is less than or equal to 0”.

16) Write a program that displays whether or not a year entered by the user is a leap year.
Reminder: leap years are years divisible by 4 but not by 100, unless they are also divisible by 400. Thus, 2000 and 2008 are leap years, whereas 1900 is not.

17) Display the sign of the product of two integers without performing the multiplication (using only comparisons). For example, the product of 5 and −7 is negative.

18) Display the sign of the sum of two integers without performing the addition (using only comparisons and negations/sign changes). For example, if 5 and −7 are added, the result is negative.

19) A vehicle rental company rents its vehicles under the following conditions:
    - Daily flat rate: €250.
    - The first 50 kilometers are free.
    - The next 450 kilometers are charged at €1.25 per kilometer.
    - Any additional kilometers are charged at €1.25 per kilometer plus a 10% surcharge.

Calculate and display the amount to be paid for a rental of n days and x kilometers traveled, where n and x are entered by the user.